*The '''Junior School''' houses classrooms for Years 4 to 6 and an assembly space named Hamilton Hall. The current buildings were built in 1963 on the site of the defunct boys' private school, Rugby House. This site was purchased in 1906, used as the Principal's residence until 1942, then as housing for staff and boarders until 1962.<ref name="FacilitiesHistory"/> 
